.TH IINDEX 1 "June 2026" "ilib @ILIB_VERSION@" "Ilib Manual"
.SH NAME
iindex \- build a thumbnail index (contact sheet) image
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B iindex
.RI [ options ]
.I outfile
.I infile1
.RI [ infile2 ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B iindex
reads one or more images and composes a single
.I outfile
image containing scaled-down thumbnails of each input arranged in a grid, with
the source file name printed under each thumbnail. The output format is chosen
from the
.I outfile
extension (see
.BR iconvert (1)).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-w N
Use a thumbnail width of
.I N
pixels (default 80). Example:
.BR \-w120 .
.TP
.BI \-H N
Use a thumbnail height of
.I N
pixels (default 60). Example:
.BR \-H120 .
.TP
.B \-f
Overwrite
.I outfile
if it already exists (otherwise the tool refuses).
.TP
.B \-s
Run silently (suppress progress output).
.TP
.BI \-html " file"
Also write an HTML client-side image map to
.I file
so the index can be used as a clickable web image.
.TP
.B \-h
Show usage information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
iindex -w120 -H120 -f index.png *.jpg
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success and non-zero on a usage error, an invalid size, or when
.I outfile
exists and
.B \-f
was not given.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR iconvert (1),
.BR iwebreprt (1)
.PP
Full API documentation: https://craigk5n.github.io/ilib/
